No fewer than 15 people sustained injuries in an accident involving a commercial bus and a private vehicle along Ada-George road in Obio/Akpor Local Council of Rivers State.
   
The accident happened late Monday night.
   
It was learnt that the incident occurred when a fully-loaded 18 –Seater commercial bus, from Mile 3 and heading to Choba, rammed into a private vehicle parked by the roadside. 
 
Although no life was lost, a woman had one of her legs chopped off in the crash. Eyewitnesses said the driver of the bus was driving recklessly when it hit the parked vehicle before it somersaulted three times. 